OL,3,CCouncil approves closure of four adult
OL,4,Cday centres despite opposition
OL,6,FBirmingham City Council has signed off
OL,7,Fplans to close four adult social care
OL,8,Fday centres for those with
OL,9,Fdisabilities despite widespread
OL,10,Fopposition from carers and service
OL,11,Fusers.
OL,13,FThe decision, approved by the council
OL,14,Fcabinet on 15 October, will result in
OL,15,Fthe closure of Beeches GOLDD, Fairway,
OL,16,FHarborne, and Heartlands day centres.
OL,18,FIt is part of a plan to address a
OL,19,F#1.95 million budget shortfall for
OL,20,F2024-25 and #3.35 million in 2025-26.
